            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.83-86_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">83</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Martin Rich
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>3/30/59.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Sir:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>First let me say that I am delighted to know of your interest in my plan for a television series based on "When the Tree Flowered".</p>
                
                <p>In answer to your question as to my plan for sharing the proceeds, I had in mind that we might share equally in the profits of this venture. However, whereas this plan is reasonable f rom my point of view in as much as I would not be required to make a cash outlay at this time; you may feel different about it when you know the r<del>e</del><add>a</add>mifications.</p>
                
                <p>It requires many hundreds of thousands of dollars to complete a project of this kind. Obviously this money must be acquired through outside sources, and the people who supply the funds for these projects are e<del>t</del><add>x</add>tremely hard bargainers. Therefore
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.83-86_0002"/>
                    
                <fw type="authorial">2.</fw>
                <fw type="curatorial">84</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Martin Rich
                </fw>
                    
                    it may be necessary to 'give away' a major share of the profits in order to acquire this financial backing. As you can see this would leave us with a small percentage to share. I must point out however that a small percentage of a successful project <hi rend="underline">could</hi> be a great deal of money. That is the gamble which we both would be taking in this instance.</p>
                
                <p>With the above in mind you may prefer some kind of cash settlement as payment for the rights...in which case I will request that you allow me a three to six month option. This would give me time to acquire financing which would include whatever cash terms we agree on.</p>
                
                <p>In any case, it would be advantageous if you give me an option for the rights so that I can start work on the project while you and I are discussing terms.</p>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.83-86_0003"/>
                
                <fw type="authorial">3.</fw>  
                <fw type="curatorial">85</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    Martin Rich
                </fw>
                
                <p>If you decide that you prefer a profit sharing arrangement...Rest assured I <del>wi</del> will do my utmost to make the best possible deal for our mutual benefit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Waiting your reply with great anticipation is</salute>
                
                    <signed>Martin Rich</signed>
                    <signed>Martin Rich.</signed>
                </closer>
                
